---
// Hero.astro
---

<style>
  .animate-slide-up { 
    animation: slideUp 0.8s ease-out forwards; 
    opacity: 0; 
    transform: translateY(20px); 
  }
  @keyframes slideUp { 
    to { 
      opacity: 1; 
      transform: translateY(0); 
    } 
  }
  .text-gradient { 
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #60a5fa, #a78bfa, #f472b6); 
    -webkit-background-clip: text; 
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; 
    background-clip: text; 
  }
  .glass-effect { 
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7); 
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px); 
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); 
  }
  .glass-light { 
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5); 
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px); 
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); 
  }
</style>

<section class="relative pt-24 pb-16 px-6 min-h-screen flex items-center content-overlay">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
    <div class="animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.3s;">
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6 text-white">
        Paying <span class="text-gradient">€50K/Year</span><br>
        to Watch Dots Moving<br>
        on a Map?
      </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.5s;">
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto font-normal leading-relaxed mb-8">
        During my 3 years in industrial R&D, I've spoken with dozens of transport and infrastructure companies. The complaint is always the same: "Why do we need €200K annual licenses just to show our assets in real-time?"
      </p>
      <div class="glass-effect rounded-2xl p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-300">There is a better way. And I know exactly how to build it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.7s;">
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center items-center">
        <a href="#analysis" class="px-8 py-4 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-blue-700 transition-all hover:scale-105 shadow-lg">
          Get Free Technical Analysis
        </a>
        <a href="#problem" class="px-8 py-4 glass-light rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-gray-800/50 transition-all text-white">
          See the Problem
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>